<item>
            <title>[LU-13734] Allow duplicate nets in kernel ip2nets syntax</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13734</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Before the MR feature was implemented, it was not possible to&lt;br/&gt;
configure multiple interfaces on the same LNet, so the ip2nets&lt;br/&gt;
syntax did not allow for this. Now that we have MR feature, we should&lt;br/&gt;
allow it to be configured via ip2nets syntax. e.g.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;o2ib(ib0) 10.10.10.1&lt;br/&gt;
o2ib(ib1) 10.10.10.2&lt;/p&gt;</description>
